  "prompt": "What is the best phone under 12k currently?",
  "response": "Choosing the best smartphone under \u20b912,000 in 2023 involves balancing features like performance, camera quality, battery life, and build quality. Here's a list of top contenders in this price range to help you make an informed decision:\n\n---\n\n### 1. **Xiaomi Redmi Note 12**\n\n**Key Specifications:**\n- **Display:** 6.67-inch FHD+ AMOLED, 120Hz refresh rate\n- **Processor:** Qualcomm Snapdragon 4 Gen 1\n- **RAM/Storage:** 4GB RAM + 64GB storage | Expandable via microSD\n- **Camera:** Triple setup - 50MP main, 8MP ultra-wide, 2MP macro\n- **Battery:** 5,000mAh with 33W fast charging\n- **Operating System:** MIUI 14 based on Android 13\n\n**Pros:**\n- Smooth display with high refresh rate\n- Strong battery performance\n- Versatile camera setup\n\n**Cons:**\n- MIUI may come with bloatware\n- Processor is adequate but not top-tier\n\n---\n\n### 2. **Realme Narzo 50**\n\n**Key Specifications:**\n- **Display:** 6.6-inch FHD+ IPS LCD, 120Hz refresh rate\n- **Processor:** MediaTek Helio G96\n- **RAM/Storage:** 4GB/128GB\n- **Camera:** Triple camera - 50MP main, 2MP macro, 2MP depth\n- **Battery:** 5,000mAh with 33W fast charging\n- **Operating System:** Realme UI 4.0 based on Android 13\n\n**Pros:**\n- High refresh rate display\n- Large storage option\n- Competitive pricing\n\n**Cons:**\n- Camera performance in low light could be better\n- Plastic build feels less premium\n\n---\n\n### 3. **Samsung Galaxy F23 5G**\n\n**Key Specifications:**\n- **Display:** 6.6-inch TFT LCD, 120Hz refresh rate\n- **Processor:** Qualcomm Snapdragon 750G\n- **RAM/Storage:** 4GB RAM + 64GB storage | Expandable via microSD\n- **Camera:** Triple setup - 50MP main, 8MP ultra-wide, 2MP macro\n- **Battery:** 5,000mAh with 25W fast charging\n- **Operating System:** One UI 5.1 based on Android 13\n\n**Pros:**\n- Reliable brand with good after-sales support\n- Decent performance for daily tasks\n- Clean software experience\n\n**Cons:**\n- TFT display is less vibrant compared to AMOLED\n- Faster charging not supported\n\n---\n\n### 4. **Motorola Moto G52**\n\n**Key Specifications:**\n- **Display:** 6.6-inch OLED, 120Hz refresh rate\n- **Processor:** Qualcomm Snapdragon 680\n- **RAM/Storage:** 4GB RAM + 128GB storage | Expandable via microSD\n- **Camera:** Triple camera - 50MP main, 2MP macro, 2MP depth\n- **Battery:** 5,000mAh with 30W fast charging\n- **Operating System:** Near-stock Android 13\n\n**Pros:**\n- Excellent display quality with OLED panel\n- Clean and user-friendly Android experience\n- Good battery life\n\n**Cons:**\n- Processor is mid-range, may lag in heavy tasks\n- Camera performance is average\n\n---\n\n### 5. **Poco M5 Pro**\n\n**Key Specifications:**\n- **Display:** 6.43-inch FHD+ AMOLED, 90Hz refresh rate\n- **Processor:** Qualcomm Snapdragon 695\n- **RAM/Storage:** 4GB RAM + 128GB storage | Expandable via microSD\n- **Camera:** Triple setup - 108MP main, 2MP macro, 2MP depth\n- **Battery:** 5,000mAh with 33W fast charging\n- **Operating System:** MIUI 14 based on Android 13\n\n**Pros:**\n- High-resolution main camera\n- Good performance for the price\n- Attractive AMOLED display\n\n**Cons:**\n- MIUI may have unnecessary apps\n- Limited availability in some regions\n\n---\n\n### **Conclusion**\n\nSelecting the best smartphone under \u20b912,000 depends on your priorities:\n\n- **For Display Quality:** **Motorola Moto G52** and **Poco M5 Pro** offer vibrant AMOLED screens.\n- **For Camera Performance:** **Poco M5 Pro** with its 108MP main camera stands out.\n- **For Battery Life and Performance:** **Xiaomi Redmi Note 12** and **Realme Narzo 50** provide reliable battery and smooth performance.\n- **For Software Experience:** **Samsung Galaxy F23 5G** and **Motorola Moto G52** offer cleaner Android experiences.\n\nConsider what features matter most to you\u2014be it camera quality, display, battery life, or overall performance\u2014and choose accordingly. All the listed phones provide good value for their price in the sub-\u20b912,000 segment.\n\n---\n\n**Note:** Prices and availability may vary based on your location and local retailers. It's advisable to check the latest prices and user reviews before making a purchase.",
